 * Zubair Kk started a discussion on a news article:
  Is there a way to add a badge to an application icon in Android? (7)

  > @Zubair: It is not possible to what you are looking for. The facebook
  > icon that you see, with the number of notifications is possible only
  > because the device firmware has facebook pre installed and the place
  > where they display the icon is not just an image view displaying the
  > icon rather, it is a view consisting of image view and text view
  > combined. It is very easy to verify the same. Connect the device on
  > which you have this facebook icon to your computer, open the DDMS
  > perspective in eclipse, from the left pane select the device and click
  > the icon of Dump View Hierarchy. This will give you a screenshot of you=
r
  > device in eclipse in which you will be able to select and see any scree=
n
  > areas view details. If you select the facebook icon there, you will see
  > what i described above.



